                            <comment id="13737756" author="terry_zhang" created="Tue, 13 Aug 2013 03:16:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;now we can see hfile will be deleted in Master file system instead be archived. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;MasterFileSystem.java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void deleteFamilyFromFS(HRegionInfo region, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] familyName)
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// archive family store files
&lt;/span&gt;    Path tableDir = FSUtils.getTableDir(rootdir, region.getTableName());
    HFileArchiver.archiveFamily(fs, conf, region, tableDir, familyName);

    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// delete the family folder
&lt;/span&gt;    Path familyDir = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Path(tableDir,
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Path(region.getEncodedName(), Bytes.toString(familyName)));
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (fs.delete(familyDir, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;) == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;) {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; IOException(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Could not delete family &quot;&lt;/span&gt;
          + Bytes.toString(familyName) + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot; from FileSystem &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; region &quot;&lt;/span&gt;
          + region.getRegionNameAsString() + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;(&quot;&lt;/span&gt; + region.getEncodedName()
          + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;)&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
    }
  }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should we use interface archiveStoreFiles instead fs.delete? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13737759" author="terry_zhang" created="Tue, 13 Aug 2013 03:23:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Now we found this issue is serious when we deleteColumn after create a snapshot.  If we restore the snapshot hlink files can not be found and table can not be enabled.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13737768" author="terry_zhang" created="Tue, 13 Aug 2013 03:35:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;deleteTable still has same problem  &lt;br/&gt;
public void deleteTable(byte[] tableName) throws IOException &lt;/p&gt;
{
    fs.delete(new Path(rootdir, Bytes.toString(tableName)), true);
  }</comment>
                            <comment id="13737773" author="lhofhansl" created="Tue, 13 Aug 2013 03:44:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So what is the actual problem?&lt;br/&gt;
The code archives the family first, then it deletes the according HFiles. So at least from the code it looks like the files are archived before the directory is deleted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the problem is that restore of snapshot fails that is a different problem.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jesse_yates&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jesse_yates&quot;&gt;Jesse Yates&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mbertozzi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mbertozzi&quot;&gt;Matteo Bertozzi&lt;/a&gt;, FYI.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13737787" author="lhofhansl" created="Tue, 13 Aug 2013 04:16:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=terry_zhang&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;terry_zhang&quot;&gt;terry zhang&lt;/a&gt;, if the snapshot restore fails it &lt;b&gt;is&lt;/b&gt; a problem and we should fix it.&lt;br/&gt;
I can change the title of the issue. Please let us know if you still have a problem with this. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
